Sentence: In fact, the critical current density of the Ag-doped sample is about 2 times the value of the corresponding undoped FeSe 0.94 material for low magnetic fields (up to 2.5 Tesla).

Although the data acquisition and the procedure for the subtraction of the magnetic background is identical for the two samples, the FeSe superconducting M(H) curve appears noisier than the curve of FeSeAg.

As shown in the inset of figure , where an enlargement of the curves in the region of the superconducting transition is reported, this value for the FeSe is approximately 8.5 K while for the FeSeAg is approximately 9 K.
